title: 820-4924 ALL_SYS_PWRGD not present
message:
Hi, I have this board with no all_sys_pwrgd, the voltages and values of the resistors around Q8150 are ok, but I still get .700v at PIN 5 and 8 and acording to me the correct value should be 1,07. at PIN 1 Q8150 I get .690v which I think is good enough.
Already removed 1 by 1 the resistors from R8164-69 leaving R8167 in place and all_sys_pwrgd doesn´t comes high. 
what am I missing?

title: 820-4924 ALL_SYS_PWRGD not present
message:
Q8150 is a redundant protection, not really needed.
Check the board removing it.

title: 820-4924 ALL_SYS_PWRGD not present
message:
0.7V is fine on the base of the BJTs inside Q8150.
[URL unfurl="true"]https://logi.wiki/index.php/ALL_SYS_PWRGD[/URL]

title: 820-4924 ALL_SYS_PWRGD not present
message:
Once Q8150 out of board, start removing the other resistors (one by one) from ALL_SYS_PWRGD.
Be sure R8167 is good.
